entry.title: Storage pressure: try automatic eviction before nagging user.
entry.content:
This CL:

* Makes write failures in the SQLite quota database flow through the

same path as write failures in QuotaClient code

* In both cases:

* try to run an eviction round first, unless one has been run

recently.

* fall back to notifying user only on the second write error,

indicating eviction didn't work to clear enough space.

* Fixes code that was intended to prevent `GetStorageCapacity()` from

being run too many times.

* Renames the method called by QuotaClients from `NotifyWriteFailed`

to `OnClientWriteFailed`

* Makes some minor stylistic fixes in the Chrome storage notification

impl

entry.title: Preserve float precision and color space info when scaling alpha.
entry.content:
Doing `flags.setColor(ScaleAlpha(color.Rgb(), alpha))`, or calling

`color.CombineWithAlpha(alpha)`, was converting the color from float

to int and back to float, dropping numerical precision and color

space information in the process.



CombineWithAlpha now keeps color information untouched and only

modifies the alpha value. It's now simple enough that it can be

trivially inlined.



For callers invoking CombineWithAlpha on a temporary (as in

`svg_object_painter.cc`) copying the `Color` object would be

wasteful. An rvalue-qualified overload is therefore provided

to modify the Color in-place if it's a temporary, saving a copy:

https://godbolt.org/z/jfxrjWeTG



This overload is measured to be 17% faster in a micro-benchmark,

available in the Patchset 5 of this CL:

https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/4415785/4..5

migrated out of the ContentSuggestionsViewController. These files

by the same directory.



The header logs several NTP metrics that are unrelated to the

content suggestions. In order for these metrics to be logged by the

new NewTabPageMetricsRecorder, the files must be moved to ui/ntp since

ui/content_suggestions does not have access to this metrics recorder.



This is also a step in the direction of removing the circular

dependency between ui/ntp and ui/content_suggestions. Only ui/ntp

should have content_suggestions dependencies, and content_suggestions

should be able to exist on its own.

entry.title: [DataRetentionPolicies] Data Retention Policies Requirements Change
entry.content:
ClearBrowsingDataOnExitList and BrowsingDataLifetime currently require SyncDisabled to be set to allow applying them. This CL relaxes the condition to disable the sync types for the respective browsing data types that need to be cleared by policy if sync and browser sign in are not disabled by policy.



This will be the new flow for applying the data retention policy:

1- If the SyncDisabled or BrowserSignin policy is set as true, then there is no need to check anything after this point as this means that all sync types are disabled, and the old logic can be followed.

2- If SyncDisabled policy and BrowserSignin are not set or set as false, then we can set the policy normally and automatically disable the sync types we need.



This change will be extended to IdleTimeoutActions policy which requires sync to be disabled as well. Thus, a shared browsing_data_policies_utils file is added to share the code for this change.

entry.title: [sync] Migrate tests away from inexistent sync-stopped case
entry.content:
Function SyncServiceImplHarness::StopSyncServiceWithoutClearingData()

and other similar cases set up a state that is unreachable by users. In

the real product nowadays, sync cannot be temporarily stopped without

more specific semantics. Either sync is paused (e.g. persistent auth

error), permanently stopped (+ signout) or the device is offline. This

patch migrates tests to adhere to more realistic scenarios.



In some cases, the logic or the whole test becomes redundant and is

deleted. TwoClientPollingSyncTest is deleted altogether because the

test has been disabled for a long time, it isn't very realistic and

would require significant changes to avoid the dependency to the

now-removed StopSyncServiceWithoutClearingData() function.



In truth, there is one corner case that allows stopping sync, similar

to what tests did before this patch. This is the case on ChromeOS, if

the sync data is cleared from the dashboard. This is a very special

case and definitely not what the tests are aiming to test.

signature to differ in those locations. If we could get rid of them

here, my life would be slightly easier.
